<%
  const formatDate = (dateStr) => {
    if (!dateStr) return "";
    const d = new Date(dateStr);
    const day = String(d.getDate()).padStart(2, "0");
    const month = String(d.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, "0");
    const year = d.getFullYear();
    return `${day}-${month}-${year}`;
  };

  const today = formatDate((form && form.issueDate) || new Date());
  const joiningDate = (form && form.joiningDate) ? formatDate(form.joiningDate) : "";

  const defaultAddress = "H.NO: 1-1/1 Mandepally, Mandepally,\nKarimnagar District, Telangana, India - 505405";

  const addressText = form && form.employeeAddress && String(form.employeeAddress).trim()
    ? form.employeeAddress
    : defaultAddress;

  const employeeName = (form && form.employeeName) ? form.employeeName : "Candidate Name";
  const firstName = employeeName.split(" ")[0] || "Candidate";
  const designation = (form && form.designation) ? form.designation : "Designation";
  const ctcAnnualNum = (form && form.ctcAnnual) ? Number(form.ctcAnnual) : 680000;
  const ctcAnnual = ctcAnnualNum.toLocaleString("en-IN");
  const ctcWords = (form && form.ctcWords) ? form.ctcWords : "Amount in words";
%>
<div class="letter-page">
  <p class="date-line"><%= today %></p>

  <p class="letter-title">Letter of Appointment</p>

  <div class="to-section">
    <p class="to-label">To,</p>
    <p class="to-name">
      <strong><%= employeeName %></strong>
    </p>
    <p class="to-address" style="white-space: pre-line;">
      <%= addressText %>
    </p>
  </div>

  <p class="dear-line">
    Dear <%= firstName %>,
  </p>

  <p class="letter-subject">
    <strong>Sub: Your Career with AMAZON IT SOLUTIONS.</strong>
  </p>

  <p class="intro-para">
    We are immensely pleased appointing you as a
    <strong><%= designation %></strong>, and have you as a
    part of Amazon IT Solutions Family. We believe your potential skills
    will be a valuable contribution to our company.
  </p>

  <p class="intro-para">
    <strong>Effective Date of Appointment:</strong> Your Date of Joining at
    <strong>“Amazon IT Solutions”</strong> is
    <strong><%= joiningDate || "dd-mm-yyyy" %></strong> and following are the
    terms and conditions:
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>1. Job Assignment:</strong> In your assignment you will be
    required to perform duties as laid down in the Job Description for your
    position.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>2. Leave Entitlement:</strong> You will be entitled to leaves as
    per Amazon IT Solutions policy mentioned in Rules and Regulations
    formulated in the Employee Hand Book of Amazon IT Solutions from time to
    time.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>3. Placement & Compensation:</strong> You will be placed in the
    appropriate responsibility level of the Company and will be entitled to
    total compensation of
    <strong>
      INR <%= ctcAnnual %>
      (<%= ctcWords %>)
    </strong>
    per Annum. Compensation will be governed by the rules of the Company, as
    applicable and amended hereafter.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <em>Note: Breakup of the fixed salary is as per the Annexure sheet.</em>
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>4. Statutory Deductions:</strong> Deductions, if any, will be
    made from your salary as per the prevailing law of the country. However,
    for your income tax you shall be personally responsible for filing
    returns etc. The company will provide you the tax deductions
    certificate, if applicable at the end of each financial year.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>5. Code of Conduct:</strong> The Code of Business Conduct and
    Ethics helps to ensure compliance with legal requirements and our
    standards as approved by the Board from time to time formulated in the
    Employee Hand Book of Amazon IT Solutions. All employees are expected to
    read and understand this Code of Business Conduct and Ethics, uphold
    these standards in day-to-day activities, comply with all applicable
    policies and procedures and adhere to these standards.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="letter-page">
  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong><br>6. Posting & Transfer:</strong> Your initial posting will be at Hyderabad. However, your
    services are liable to be transferred, at the sole discretion of Management, as the company may
    determine, to any department / section, location, associate, sister concern or subsidiary, at any
    place in India or abroad, whether existing today or which may come up in future. In such a case, you will be
    governed by the terms and conditions of service applicable at the new placement location.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>7. Probation:</strong> You will be on probation for a period of six months. The period of probation can
    be extended at the discretion of the Management and you will continue to be on probation till an order of confirmation has been issued.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>8. Full Time Employment:</strong> Your position is a full-time employment with the Company and you
    shall devote yourself exclusively to the business and interests of the company. You will not take up any other work for remuneration (part time shareholder’s or director work in an advisory capacity), be or become directly or indirectly (accept the shareholder / debenture holder) in any other trade or business during your employment with the company, without written permission from the Management of the Company. You will also not seek membership of any local or public bodies without first obtaining specific permission from the Management.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>9. Confidentiality:</strong> You will not, at any time, during the employment or after, without the
    consent of the Management disclose or divulge or make public, except on legal obligations, any information concerning the Company’s affairs or make any publication or research carried out, whether the results are stated to or becomes known to you in the course of your service or otherwise.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>10. Intellectual Property:</strong> If you conceive any new or advanced method of improving designs / systems / formulae / systems etc., in relation to the company’s operations, the development shall be fully communicated to the company and will be, and remain, the sole right / property of the company.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>11. Duties & Discipline:</strong> You are to work in the organization subject to the rules and
    regulations of the organization as laid down in relation to conduct, discipline and other matters.
    You will always be held responsible and liable to perform your office duties and conduct yourself
    according to the expectations of the company. An onsite opportunity may be provided to a period of 12 months (UK/US) preferably based on project requirement, specific skills, expansion, for a short or long term.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>12. Past Records:</strong> If any declaration given or information furnished by you to the company proves to be false, or if you are found to have wilfully suppressed any material information, in such case, your name liable to be removed from service without any notice.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>13. Termination of employment:</strong>
  </p>
  
  <p class="letter-section1">
    13.1 During the probationary period and any extension thereof, services can be terminated by either party by giving two months notice in writing or gross salary in lieu thereof, only by the employer and this does not apply for the employee. However, on confirmation the services can be terminated by either party by giving Ninety Days (90 days) notice in writing or gross salary in lieu thereof, only by the employer and this does not apply for the employee. Giving out of notice period is up to the sole discretion of the management.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="letter-page">

  <p class="letter-section1">
    <br>13.2 Upon termination of employment, you will immediately hand over to the Company all correspondence, specifications, formulae, books, documents, market data, cost data, drawings, office or records belonging to the Company or relating to its business and shall not retain in any form copies of these items.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section1">
    13.3 Upon termination of employment, you will also return all company property which may be in your possession.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>14. General Conditions:</strong> You will be bound by the following:
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section1">
    14.1 You will not engage in any unlawful or any subversive activity while in the service of Amazon IT Solutions.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section1">
    14.2 Amazon IT Solutions will expect you to work in section / department / process / project in which you are placed with a high standard of initiative, efficiency and economy.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section1">
    14.3 You shall not under any circumstances either directly or indirectly receive or accept for own benefit any commission, rebate, discount, gift or profit of any nature from any person, company or firm having business transaction with Amazon IT Solutions.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section1">
    14.4 You will, in all respects, be governed by the rules and regulations applicable to your category of employees from time to time.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>15. Non-Disclosure:</strong> You will not disclose by word of mouth or otherwise, particulars or details of business or trade. We are immensely pleased appointing you as Security Analyst and having you as part of our team. Any confidential information of business coming to your knowledge by virtue of your being in the employment of Amazon IT Solutions is strictly confidential.
  </p>

  <p class="letter-section">
    <strong>16. Acceptance:</strong> If you accept the above terms and conditions of the service, please signify your acceptance by signing up the photo copy of this Appointment Letter thereof otherwise this letter of appointment will be deemed to have been withdrawn and cancelled.
  </p>

  <div class="signature-section"><br>
    <p>
      For Amazon IT Solutions.<br><br><br>
      <br>
      <strong>Chakravarthy Devarakonda</strong><br>
      Manager – Human Resources
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
